1.text: When the last letter of a singular noun is y and the letter before y is a consonant, its plural is formed by changing y to ies.
1.ssml: <speak><prosody rate='slow'>When the last letter of a singular noun is y and the letter before y is a consonant, its plural is formed by changing y to ies.</prosody></speak>

3.text: baby babies (last letter - y, consonant - b) lady ladies city cities fly flies
3.ssml: <speak><prosody rate='slow'>baby babies (last letter - y, consonant - b) lady ladies city cities fly flies</prosody></speak>

4.text: Some nouns ending with f or fe form their plural by adding ves.
4.ssml: <speak><prosody rate='slow'>Some nouns ending with f or fe form their plural by adding ves.</prosody></speak>

6.text: leaf leaves knife knives life lives calf calves
6.ssml: <speak><prosody rate='slow'>leaf leaves knife knives life lives calf calves</prosody></speak>

7.text: Some nouns have different singular and plural forms.
7.ssml: <speak><prosody rate='slow'>Some nouns have different singular and plural forms.</prosody></speak>

9.text: man men woman women child children tooth teeth foot feet mouse mice
